Marian Foik (6 October 1933 in Ruda lska  May 20, 2005 in Warszawa) was a Polish athlete who mainly competed in the 100 metres. He competed at the 1964 Summer Olympics held in Tokyo, Japan, participating in the 4 x 100 metre relay. With his team mates Andrzej Zieliski, Wiesaw Maniak and Marian Dudziak, he won the silver medal. 
